library(tseries)

# Data: Seoul Metro Daily Data
metro <- read.csv('./data/seoul_metro.csv')
city <- metro$CityHall

ts.plot(city)

# Forecasting 14 days
city_train <- city[1:1812]
city_test <- city[1813:1826]

# tbats with multi-seasonality
city_ts <- ts(city_train, frequency=7)
city_msts <- msts(city_train, seasonal.periods = c(7, 365))

# tbats   .
tbats_ts <- tbats(city_ts)
tbats_msts <- tbats(city_msts)

fcst_ts <- forecast(tbats_ts, h=14)
fcst_msts <- forecast(tbats_msts, h=14)
par(mfrow=c(2,1))
plot(fcst_ts)
plot(fcst_msts)

mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(fcst_ts$mean) - as.numeric(city_test)) / as.numeric(city_test))
## [1] 90.61247
mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(fcst_msts$mean) - as.numeric(city_test)) / as.numeric(city_test))
## [1] 91.2062
par(mfrow=c(1,1))

# forecasdt 365 days
city_train2 <- city[1:1461]
city_test2 <- city[1462:1826]
city_ts2 <- ts(city_train2, frequency=7)
city_msts2 <- msts(city_train2, seasonal.periods = c(7, 365))
city_msts2_2 <- msts(city_train2, seasonal.periods = c(7, 30, 365))

tbat_ts_2 <- tbats(city_ts2)
tbat_msts_2 <- tbats(city_msts2)
tbat_msts_2_2 <- tbats(city_msts2_2)

fcst_ts_2 <- forecast(tbat_ts_2, h=365)
fcst_msts_2 <- forecast(tbat_msts_2, h=365)
fcst_msts_2_2 <- forecast(tbat_msts_2_2, h=365)

par(mfrow=c(3,1))
plot(fcst_ts_2)
plot(fcst_msts_2)
plot(fcst_msts_2_2)

mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(fcst_ts_2$mean) - as.numeric(city_test2)) / as.numeric(city_test2))
## [1] 83.506
mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(fcst_msts_2$mean) - as.numeric(city_test2)) / as.numeric(city_test2))
## [1] 85.42365

## [1] 84.54537

  1. Fourier Series: Sine, Cosine Function .

  2. auto.arima Fourier Series .
  • auto.arima
  • frequency 350 Multi-seasonaliy Fourier Series .
  • auto.arima Fourier term seasonality
  • auto.arima xreg .
city_train3 <- city[1:1461]
city_test3 <- city[1462:1826]

city_msts_3 <- msts(city_train3, seasonal.periods = c(7, 365))

fourier_arima <- fourier(city_msts_3, K=c(3, 10))
fourier_arima_reg <- fourier(city_msts_3, K=c(3, 10), h=365)
arima_msts <- auto.arima(city_msts_3, seasonal = F, xreg=fourier_arima)
fcst_msts_3 <- forecast(arima_msts, xreg=fourier_arima_reg, h=365)
plot(fcst_msts_3)

mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(fcst_msts_3$mean) - as.numeric(city_test3)) / as.numeric(city_test3))
## [1] 71.88158
